FlexCard SDK Data Source

Use a SDK, such as the Salesforce Industries Digital Commerce SDK, to reuse business logic and focus on creating UI. The SDK calls an API, processes the response, and gives it back to the client.

Beginning Winter ‘23, SDK data source is not supported with Managed Package Runtime disabled. If you open a FlexCard created with an SDK data source, you’ll see an error in the FlexCard Designer.

See Salesforce Industries Digital Commerce SDK documentation.

Create and upload a static resource for the SDK to appear as a data source option. Configure the SDK data source for your FlexCard in the FlexCard Designer.

To use an SDK as a data source:

1. Create a static resource named OmniStudioActionRegistry containing the SDK configuration.
2. Configure a data source using methods from the SDK to provide data for the FlexCard.
title: FlexCard SDK Data Source Configuration
